  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We formulate a wilsonian renormalization group theory for the imbalanced Fermi gas. The theory is able to recover quantitatively well-established results in both the weak-coupling and the strong-coupling (unitarity) limit. We determine for the latter case the line of second-order phase transitions of the imbalanced Fermi gas and in particular the location of the tricritical point. We obtain good agreement with the recent experiments of Y. Shin {\it et al}. arXiv:0709.3027 [cond-mat].</subfield>
